[src:atc-code-v06/atc-code-a] Codes for veterinary use (ATCvet codes) can be created by placing the letter Q in front of the human ATC code: for example, **QA**.
[src:atc-code-v06/atc-code-a] National versions of the ATC classification may include additional codes not present in this list, which follows the WHO version.
[src:atc-code-v06/atc-code-b] Codes for veterinary use (ATCvet codes) can be created by placing the letter Q in front of the human ATC code: for example, **QB**.
[src:atc-code-v06/atc-code-c] Codes for veterinary use (ATCvet codes) can be created by placing the letter Q in front of the human ATC code: for example, **QC**.
[src:atc-code-v06/atc-code-d] Codes for veterinary use (ATCvet codes) can be created by placing the letter Q in front of the human ATC code: for example, **QD**.
[src:atc-code-v06/atc-code-d] ATCvet codes without corresponding human ATC codes are cited with the leading Q in the following list.
[src:atc-code-v06/atc-code-g] Codes for veterinary use (ATCvet codes) can be created by placing the letter Q in front of the human ATC code: for example, **QG**.
[src:atc-code-v06/atc-code-h] Codes for veterinary use (ATCvet codes) can be created by placing the letter Q in front of the human ATC code: for example, **QH**.
[src:atc-code-v06/atc-code-j] Codes for veterinary use (ATCvet codes) can be created by placing the letter Q in front of the human ATC code: for example, **QJ**.
[src:atc-code-v06/atc-code-v06] Codes for veterinary use (ATCvet codes) can be created by placing the letter Q in front of the human ATC code: for example, **QV06**.
